<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1826" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1826">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.001/6.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>This morning at nine o’clock in the National Palace President Meléndez
                            turned over the Executive power to the First Designate, Dr. Alfonso
                            Quiñónez M.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tennant</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>